The facility maintains required written emergency planning documents.  Written ammonia emergency action procedures are detailed in the GCC ?Thirty Minute Plan?.  The Hazardous Material Business Plan and the Emergency Action Plan detail procedures for non-responding personnel.  The Hazardous Material Business Plan contains procedures for small spills and procedures for materials other than ammonia.  Each of these Plans are maintained on-site and updated on a regular basis.

1.6   Planned changes to improve safety

The primary mechanisms to identify and plan safety improvements include (but are not limited to):
?Process Hazard Analysis revalidation/update;
?Cal/ARP Seismic Assessment;
?Compliance Audits;
?Routine maintenance (Mechanical Integrity Program);
?Triennial IIAR Bulletin 109 Inspections; and
?GCC Inspection Protocol

Each of the Programs above may result in recommendations ranging from capital improvements to routine maintenance of the plant.  Work Orders are established in parallel to identified needs.  Current planned changes to improve safety include:
?Update and upgrade of the RMP/PSM Documents;
?Online Ammonia PSM Technical Training Courses (Ammonia Technicians);
?Improved/updated SOP?s;
?Improved tagging and documentation of process valves;
?Improved labeling of process piping; 
?Improved maintenance schedule;
?Seismic Improvements; and
?Programmable Logic Controller Upgrade

Implementation of these measures has commenced according to the schedule set by the management of GCC.
